Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech in Phoenix, Arizona, where he thanked the state for its support of President Trump and discussed various issues, including the ongoing Tinder Fire in Coconino County. Pence praised Governor Doug Ducey for his leadership and highlighted the progress that Arizona has made under his administration, such as job creation and tax cuts. He also touched on topics such as border security, law enforcement, and the economy. Pence encouraged the audience to spread the message of the administration's accomplishments and urged them to pray for America. He ended his speech by expressing confidence in the future of the country.